        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks for AG’s Japan memoir [<hi rend="italic">Mem. Am. Acad. Arts &amp; Sci.</hi> 6 (1857–9): 377–452]. Does not think AG’s arguments for a warm post-glacial period are sufficient, but will not be sorry to be proved wrong.</p> 
            <p>Believes natural selection explains many classes of facts which repeated creation does not.</p> 
<p>Writes of some responses to the <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>.</p> 
        </abstract>
